{"parse":{"title":"Adam Sabra","pageid":48659887,"revid":835992905,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Adam Sabra</b> is professor and King Abdul Aziz Ibn Saud Chair in Islamic Studies at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_California\" title=\"University of California\">University of California</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Selected_publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Adam_Sabra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Sabra received his Ph.D. from <a href=\"/wiki/Princeton_University\" title=\"Princeton University\">Princeton University</a> in 1998.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Adam_Sabra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Adam Sabra is professor and King Abdul Aziz Ibn Saud Chair in Islamic Studies at the University of California.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_publications\">Selected publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Adam_Sabra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Selected publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>Poverty and Charity in Medieval Islam: Mamluk Egypt, 1250-1517</i>. Cambridge: <a href=\"/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press\" title=\"Cambridge University Press\">Cambridge University Press</a>, 2000 (paperback edition)</li>\n<li>With Roxani Eleni Margariti and Petra M. Sijpesteijn (eds.), <i>Histories of the Middle East: Studies in Middle Eastern Society, Economy and Law in Honor of A. L. Udovitch</i>. Leiden: Brill, 2010.</li>\n<li>With Richard J. McGregor (eds.), <i>Le d\u00e9veloppement du soufisme en \u00c9gypte \u00e0 l\u2019\u00e9poque mamlouke</i>. Cairo: <a href=\"/wiki/Institut_Fran%C3%A7ais_d%27Arch%C3%A9ologie_Orientale\" title=\"Institut Fran\u00e7ais d&#39;Arch\u00e9ologie Orientale\">Institut Fran\u00e7ais d'Arch\u00e9ologie Orientale</a>, 2006.</li>\n<li>\u201cIbn Hazm\u2019s Literalism: A Critique of Islamic Legal Theory,\u201d in <i>al-Qantara</i>, XXVIII/1 (enero-junio 2007), pp.&#160;7\u201340, XXVIII/2 (julio-diciembre 2007), pp.&#160;307\u2013348.</li>\n<li><i>The Guidebook for Gullible Jurists and Mendicants to the Conditions for Befriendig Emirs and, The Abbreviated Guidebook for Gullible Jurists and Mendicants to the Conditions for Befriendig Emirs</i> by \u2018Abd al-Wahh\u0101b ibn A\u1e25mad \u2018Al\u012b al-Sha\u2018r\u0101n\u012b</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Adam_Sabra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.history.ucsb.edu/faculty/adam-sabra\">Adam Sabra.</a> Department of History, University of California, Santa Barbara. Retrieved 28 November 2015.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg/30px-Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg/45px-Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg/60px-Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"606\" data-file-height=\"606\" /></a></td><td><i>This biography of an academic is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Adam_Sabra&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Academic-bio-stub\" title=\"Template:Academic-bio-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Academic-bio-stub\" title=\"Te